Overview

Walton is the only child of John T. Walton, the second son of Wal-Mart founder Sam Walton. Lukas was the biggest beneficiary of his father's will and he's calculated to have received a 4 percent stake in the Bentonville, Arkansas-based retailer after John Walton died in 2005. His mother, Christy, inherited a 2 percent stake.

