Biography
Grandfather, Samuel Moore Walton, grew up in Columbia, Missouri; in 1940, he joined J.C. Penney as a Management Trainee. Two years later, Samuel was drafted into the U.S. Army Intelligence Corps. After his discharge from the army, Samuel took a $20,000 loan from his father-in-law and purchased a Ben Franklin variety store in Newport, Arkansas. After a dispute with his landlord, Samuel relocated his store to Bentonville, Arkansas in 1950. He subsequently opened several Ben Franklin stores in Arkansas, Kansas and ...
